const shrunkenVictims = [
  { id:'brian', name:'Brian', birthday:'Unknown', gender:'Male', nationality:'US American', occupation:'Unemployed', hair:'Unknown', eyes:'Unknown', height:'Unknown', weight:'Unknown', chest:'Unknown', waist:'Unknown', hips:'Unknown', firstAppearance:'Strange Behaviours', status:'deceased', setting:'Shrunken / Prey', stories:['Strange Behaviours'], deathCause:'Digested alive', killer:'Ashley Taylor', intelligence:30, fear:85, vocalness:15, obedient:90, desire:100, iconicQuote:'"I\'ve been looking forward to this all my life." — Brian to Ashley, Strange Behaviours', bio:'Brian is the primary perspective character of Strange Behaviours — a shrunken US American male and self-described vorarephile. He is unemployed and described as a "loser" by his own admission: he works a dead-end job that barely covers expenses, spends his free time gaming, smoking marijuana, and consuming vore-related pornography. He was previously hospitalised for several months following a nervous breakdown, accumulating medical debt. He suspects his shrinking was related to his being classified as a societal "deviant" or economic burden by Vortex\'s criteria. Brian has fantasised about being eaten his entire life, and finds himself profoundly conflicted when his fantasy becomes reality: genuinely terrified of death, but also more aroused than he has ever been, particularly because his purchaser, Ashley Taylor, is exceptionally beautiful by his standards. Their conversation — the only time in the story Ashley pauses for a shrinkie — is one of the most unique exchanges in the series. She ultimately honours his request to be swallowed whole. He experiences his death from the inside in gruesome detail, eventually dying from a combination of acid burns, drowning in stomach chyme, and physical implosion under pressure.' },
  { id:'megan-sanders', name:'Megan Sanders', birthday:'Unknown', gender:'Female', nationality:'US American', occupation:'Lawyer', hair:'Unknown', eyes:'Unknown', height:'Unknown', weight:'Unknown', chest:'Unknown', waist:'Unknown', hips:'Unknown', firstAppearance:'Strange Behaviours', status:'deceased', setting:'Shrunken / Prey', stories:['Strange Behaviours'], deathCause:'Swallowed alive by Ashley Taylor', killer:'Ashley Taylor', intelligence:40, fear:95, vocalness:85, obedient:10, desire:0, iconicQuote:'"[Pleading for her life mid-sentence as Ashley swallows her]" — Megan Sanders, Strange Behaviours', bio:'Megan Sanders was a lawyer who had been working on cold cases involving the disappearances of local journalists. This investigation drew the ire of both the Department of Justice and VortexFoods™, resulting in her being shrunken and packaged. She is the first shrinkie Ashley consumes in Strange Behaviours — plucked from the box, she begins to plead for her life as Ashley heads downstairs, but Ashley ignores her completely, tossing her into her mouth mid-sentence and casually swallowing her during patio furniture assembly. The narrative notes bitterly that nobody would ever hear about her or the journalists she was investigating.' },
  { id:'timothy-walker', name:'Timothy Walker', birthday:'Unknown', gender:'Male', nationality:'US American', occupation:'Convicted serial killer', hair:'Unknown', eyes:'Unknown', height:'Unknown', weight:'Unknown', chest:'Unknown', waist:'Unknown', hips:'Unknown', firstAppearance:'Strange Behaviours', status:'deceased', setting:'Shrunken / Prey', stories:['Strange Behaviours'], deathCause:'Swallowed alive by Ashley Taylor', killer:'Ashley Taylor', intelligence:20, fear:90, vocalness:85, obedient:10, desire:0, iconicQuote:'"I haven\'t done anything!" — Timothy Walker lying to Ashley, Strange Behaviours', bio:'Timothy Walker was a drifter who murdered several hitchhikers over the course of several years. He had been sentenced to death only the week before the events of Strange Behaviours, with his death sentence to be carried out by VortexFoods™ in the form of being packaged and sold. He begs for his life and claims he "hasn\'t done anything" when Ashley reaches for him — a lie she calls out with contempt. Ashley will read about his "execution" on her phone the following day while disposing of his remains, briefly thinking to herself that justice has been done.' },
  { id:'max', name:'Max', birthday:'Unknown', gender:'Male', nationality:'German', occupation:'Student / Volunteer', hair:'Blonde (long)', eyes:'Brown', height:'Unknown', weight:'Unknown', chest:'Unknown', waist:'Unknown', hips:'Unknown', firstAppearance:'An American Nightmare', status:'deceased', setting:'Shrunken / Prey', stories:['An American Nightmare'], deathCause:'Digested alive by Ashley Taylor (unknowingly) mid-flight over the Arctic Circle', killer:'Ashley Taylor', intelligence:70, fear:95, vocalness:90, obedient:5, desire:45, iconicQuote:'"No! Please don\'t! Ashley!" — Max screaming as Ashley swallows him, An American Nightmare', bio:'Max is the primary perspective character of An American Nightmare — a tall, long-haired, rakishly stubbled German student with brown eyes who is travelling to the US to visit a friend on the West Coast before a volunteer project saving sea turtles in Guatemala. He is thoughtful, politically conscious, and deeply opposed to VortexFoods™ on moral grounds. He meets Ashley Taylor at passport control at the airport and they share a brief, warm connection over their shared flight. He is detained when border control finds a forgotten bag of cannabis in his backpack. A senior officer invokes "Section V" — handing him to Vortex operatives in the airport car park — and he is rendered unconscious, shrunk, and packaged into a Vortex promotional box loaded onto the very plane Ashley is boarding. He spends the flight in the catering trolley watching Kelly Lewis eat shrinkies. He is served directly to Ashley\'s tray as part of the Vortex in-flight promotional dinner. He desperately hammers on the cubicle window and screams her name, but she cannot hear him. She swallows him whole, and he dies of digestion inside her stomach somewhere over the Arctic Circle. Ashley never learns what happened to him.' },
  { id:'thilo-busch', name:'Thilo Busch', birthday:'Unknown', gender:'Male', nationality:'German', occupation:'Journalist', hair:'Unknown', eyes:'Unknown', height:'Unknown', weight:'Unknown', chest:'Unknown', waist:'Unknown', hips:'Unknown', firstAppearance:'An American Nightmare', status:'deceased', setting:'Shrunken / Prey', stories:['An American Nightmare'], deathCause:'Swallowed whole by Kelly Lewis in the galley', killer:'Kelly Lewis', intelligence:50, fear:95, vocalness:90, obedient:10, desire:0, iconicQuote:'"[Begging for his life as Kelly tosses him into her mouth]" — Thilo Busch, An American Nightmare', bio:'Thilo Busch was a German journalist who had been on VortexFoods™\'s hit list for an extended period of time. He had been preparing to report on the business practices of a Peruvian "recruitment agency" acting on behalf of Vortex — likely documenting forced disappearances and the supply of victims for the shrinking program. Vortex seized the opportunity to intercept him when he checked in at the airport. He is the first shrunken person consumed in An American Nightmare, eaten casually by Kelly Lewis in the galley between service rounds. His social media profiles and blog vanish from the internet simultaneously, as if he never existed. Max watches his death through the cubicle window.' },
  { id:'heiko-brandt', name:'Heiko Brandt', birthday:'Unknown', gender:'Male', nationality:'German', occupation:'Convicted criminal', hair:'Unknown', eyes:'Unknown', height:'Unknown', weight:'Unknown', chest:'Unknown', waist:'Unknown', hips:'Unknown', firstAppearance:'An American Nightmare', status:'deceased', setting:'Shrunken / Prey', stories:['An American Nightmare'], deathCause:'Tossed into mouth and swallowed by Kayla Hayes during in-flight dinner service', killer:'Kayla Hayes', intelligence:30, fear:90, vocalness:70, obedient:15, desire:0, iconicQuote:'"[Daydreaming about the Pacific Ocean]" — Heiko\'s last thoughts before being eaten, An American Nightmare', bio:'Heiko Brandt was a German member of a violent biker gang, convicted of aggravated assault and sentenced to prison. He was part of a group of shrunken people delivered to the airport from a nearby prison, packaged into Vortex promotional boxes for the in-flight service. In prison, he had spent his days daydreaming about going on a bike tour along the US West Coast and swimming in the Pacific — a dream the story notes will technically be fulfilled in a fashion, as the water from his digested body eventually reaches the ocean via Kayla\'s sewage system, the treatment plant, and the sea.' },
  { id:'paige-wright', name:'Paige Wright', birthday:'Unknown', gender:'Female', nationality:'US American', occupation:'Activist', hair:'Unknown', eyes:'Unknown', height:'Unknown', weight:'Unknown', chest:'Unknown', waist:'Unknown', hips:'Unknown', firstAppearance:'A Matter of Principle', status:'deceased', setting:'Shrunken / Prey', stories:['A Matter of Principle'], deathCause:'Digested alive by Hannah Lindquist — first stomach acid exposure, then drowned in chyme while holding Jordan', killer:'Hannah Lindquist', intelligence:80, fear:85, vocalness:90, obedient:5, desire:55, iconicQuote:'"No! Please God, I don\'t wanna di—" — Paige Wright\'s final words before Hannah swallows her, A Matter of Principle', bio:'Paige Wright is the primary prey perspective character of A Matter of Principle — an anti-Vortex activist and the emotional heart of the resistance storyline. She organised and participated in a raid on one of Vortex\'s largest North American processing facilities, intending to sabotage the machinery and free prisoners without violence. Her brother Dylan brought guns without her consent, and their mission is betrayed by Seo-Yun Park, who had been embedded as an informant. After being shrunken and packaged, Paige ends up in a display box at the beachfront Vortex restaurant where she recognises her co-worker Rachel Cohen. She manages to survive through several near-deaths — including almost being swallowed by Rachel — but ultimately cannot prevent Hannah Lindquist, an incoming college freshman she had briefly liked for her apparent conscience, from eating her as her first tiny. Paige spends her final minutes trapped in Hannah\'s stomach with Jordan, the two holding each other in the churning acid. She had earned a degree from the same college Hannah is about to start, and her social media profile is found by Hannah that evening while she pleasures herself. Her full name comes from that search.' },
  { id:'dylan', name:'Dylan', birthday:'Unknown', gender:'Male', nationality:'US American', occupation:'Activist', hair:'Unknown', eyes:'Dark brown', height:'Unknown', weight:'Unknown', chest:'Unknown', waist:'Unknown', hips:'Unknown', firstAppearance:'A Matter of Principle', status:'deceased', setting:'Shrunken / Prey', stories:['A Matter of Principle'], deathCause:'Swallowed whole by Ashley Taylor, then suffocated inside her stomach during a bite of her hamburger', killer:'Ashley Taylor', intelligence:60, fear:90, vocalness:80, obedient:5, desire:0, iconicQuote:'"He knew who he was working for. We all make our own decisions, and some of those come with a price tag." — Dylan (full-sized) defending shooting the guard, A Matter of Principle', bio:'Dylan is Paige Wright\'s older brother and a key figure in the activist raid on the Vortex facility. He brought firearms against his sister\'s wishes and personally shot and killed a security guard who turned out to be a recent new father. He is described as having deep brown eyes and showing a complex mixture of fear, sadness, and determination. After being shrunken and placed in a Vortex box, he attempts to help Jordan escape their cubicles before Ashley Taylor casually spots him and swallows him — sucking on him briefly before gulping him down. He dies suffocated inside Ashley\'s stomach sometime while she finishes her burger. His sister Paige watches his death helplessly.' },
  { id:'miguel', name:'Miguel', birthday:'Unknown', gender:'Male', nationality:'Unknown', occupation:'Activist', hair:'Unknown', eyes:'Unknown', height:'Unknown', weight:'Unknown', chest:'Unknown', waist:'Unknown', hips:'Unknown', firstAppearance:'A Matter of Principle', status:'deceased', setting:'Shrunken / Prey', stories:['A Matter of Principle'], deathCause:'Swallowed alive by Rachel Cohen, drowned in stomach contents', killer:'Rachel Cohen', intelligence:55, fear:95, vocalness:95, obedient:5, desire:0, iconicQuote:'"Help me, Paige. Don\'t let her eat me!" — Miguel screaming as Rachel lifts him, A Matter of Principle', bio:'Miguel is a member of Paige Wright\'s activist team described as a hulk of a man. During the raid, he broke through double doors using his strength and was the one who first asked Dylan what to do in the firefight. After being shrunken and packaged, he is the first person from Paige\'s group to be eaten — casually sucked in by Rachel Cohen, his screams becoming muffled before he is swallowed. Paige witnesses this helplessly from her cubicle, barely failing to reach him in time. Rachel refuses Paige\'s desperate plea to vomit him back up, citing vanity. He drowns in her stomach contents not long after.' },
  { id:'jordan', name:'Jordan', birthday:'Unknown', gender:'Female', nationality:'US American', occupation:'Activist', hair:'Unknown', eyes:'Unknown', height:'Unknown', weight:'Unknown', chest:'Unknown', waist:'Unknown', hips:'Unknown', firstAppearance:'A Matter of Principle', status:'deceased', setting:'Shrunken / Prey', stories:['A Matter of Principle'], deathCause:'Drowned in Hannah Lindquist\'s stomach acid while held by Paige Wright', killer:'Hannah Lindquist', intelligence:55, fear:90, vocalness:85, obedient:10, desire:0, iconicQuote:'"I\'m afraid." — Jordan to Paige in their final moments, A Matter of Principle', bio:'Jordan is Dylan\'s girlfriend and a fierce, bellicose personality in the activist group who brought her own firearm to the raid. She is described as short-tempered and fearless before capture. After being shrunken, she is swallowed by Hannah Lindquist as her second victim — eaten immediately after Paige. Inside Hannah\'s stomach, she finds Paige in the dark and the two hold each other through the terror of acid, food waves, and the grinding horror of digestion. Jordan, who previously clashed with Paige due to competing for Dylan\'s attention, shows an unexpected vulnerability in her final moments. She and Paige die together, their bodies eventually broken apart by Hannah\'s peristaltic contractions and deposited as waste the next morning.' },
  { id:'tyler', name:'Tyler', birthday:'Unknown', gender:'Male', nationality:'US American', occupation:'Activist / Computer specialist', hair:'Unknown', eyes:'Unknown', height:'Unknown', weight:'Unknown', chest:'Unknown', waist:'Unknown', hips:'Unknown', firstAppearance:'A Matter of Principle', status:'deceased', setting:'Shrunken / Prey', stories:['A Matter of Principle'], deathCause:'Swept away in Hannah Lindquist\'s stomach after being swallowed whole', killer:'Hannah Lindquist', intelligence:65, fear:100, vocalness:100, obedient:0, desire:0, iconicQuote:'"Someone help me please! I want to go home!" — Tyler screaming inside Hannah\'s stomach, A Matter of Principle', bio:'Tyler is the activist group\'s computer specialist, a painfully shy and insecure young man with various phobias who was reluctant to join the raid but was convinced by Paige that they needed his tech skills. He is swallowed by Hannah as her third named victim, and the experience of being eaten alive apparently breaks his mind entirely — inside Hannah\'s stomach he cries incoherently for his mother and screams for help. Paige and Jordan try to call out to him but his voice is drowned out by a wave of food and chyme before they can reach him. Hannah notes he had reminded her of a former classmate she had pitied and now realises she actually despised.' },
  { id:'diane', name:'Diane', birthday:'Unknown', gender:'Female', nationality:'US American', occupation:'Unknown', hair:'Unknown', eyes:'Unknown', height:'Unknown', weight:'Unknown', chest:'Unknown', waist:'Unknown', hips:'Unknown', firstAppearance:'A Matter of Principle', status:'deceased', setting:'Shrunken / Prey', stories:['A Matter of Principle'], deathCause:'Swallowed whole by Ashley Taylor after pleading with Hannah', killer:'Ashley Taylor', intelligence:50, fear:95, vocalness:90, obedient:0, desire:0, iconicQuote:'"Please, don\'t eat me, Hannah. This is all some terrible mistake." — Diane pleading on Ashley\'s palm, A Matter of Principle', bio:'Diane is a shrunken woman several years older than Hannah, Ashley, and Rachel. She is the first tiny Ashley offers Hannah as a way of getting her to try eating shrinkies. Diane makes direct eye contact with Hannah and begs for her life by name, claiming to be an innocent victim of a terrible mistake. Both Rachel and Ashley roll their eyes at this — Rachel calling it the standard line criminals use. Before Hannah can respond either way, Ashley drops Diane into her mouth and swallows her instantly, noting that letting shrinkies speak always causes trouble. Diane\'s fate illustrates the arbitrary, impersonal nature of death in the Vortex world.' },
  { id:'arthur', name:'Arthur', birthday:'Unknown', gender:'Male', nationality:'US American', occupation:'Freelance programmer / card trader', hair:'Unknown', eyes:'Unknown', height:'Unknown', weight:'Unknown', chest:'Unknown', waist:'Unknown', hips:'Unknown', firstAppearance:"Good for Goodness' Sake", status:'deceased', setting:'Shrunken / Prey', stories:["Good for Goodness' Sake"], deathCause:"Used intimately by Hannah Lindquist, then swallowed whole and digested alive", killer:'Hannah Lindquist', intelligence:50, fear:95, vocalness:90, obedient:10, desire:80, iconicQuote:'"Hannah! I\'m down here! It\'s me, Arthur!" — Arthur desperately screaming to be recognised, Good for Goodness\' Sake', bio:"Arthur is the primary prey perspective character of Good for Goodness' Sake — a shrunken US American male and Hannah Lindquist's former high school classmate. He is a socially isolated young man who spent the years after graduation living in a cheap apartment near their hometown, surviving on freelance coding and trading rare Japanese collectible cards, and spending most of his time gaming, watching anime, and masturbating. He carried a long-standing, unrequited crush on Hannah throughout school — she was one of the few people who treated him with basic decency, occasionally eating lunch with him out of pity, though she privately found his company exhausting. He falls into substantial debt through bad cryptocurrency investments and is shrunk by Vortex that very evening. He ends up in a Vortex airport display case and is bought by Hannah — recognising her just as she zips the box into her backpack. He spends the journey home in a state of desperate hope. He is tumbled onto Hannah's plate of Christmas cookies and screams her name until almost being swallowed, at which point she recognises him at last. Rather than save him, Hannah is overpowered by the dynamic and uses him for intimate pleasure, then leaves him inside her for several hours during family dinner. When she finally retrieves him, he begs for his life and a second chance, citing their friendship — she dismisses this with genuine-sounding sadness, calling it a new world with no place for people like him. He is dropped alive into her mouth and dies over the course of the night inside her stomach, his remains flushed down the toilet Christmas morning. His desire bar reflects the involuntary arousal he experiences when first seeing Hannah's body, even amid his terror." },
  { id:'joe-gunderson', name:'Joe Gunderson', birthday:'Unknown', gender:'Male', nationality:'US American', occupation:'Convicted car thief', hair:'Unknown', eyes:'Unknown', height:'Unknown', weight:'Unknown', chest:'Unknown', waist:'Unknown', hips:'Unknown', firstAppearance:'Checking Out', status:'deceased', setting:'Shrunken / Prey', stories:['Checking Out'], deathCause:"Eaten by Cassandra Davis; washed down with morning coffee", killer:'Cassandra Davis', intelligence:45, fear:80, vocalness:85, obedient:5, desire:15, iconicQuote:'"You lying bastards!" — Joe muttering as the plastic foil is removed from his box, Checking Out', bio:"Joe Gunderson is a shrunken US American convicted of multiple counts of grand theft auto. He had been serving a protracted prison sentence when he and other inmates were lured into accepting a supposed 'rehabilitation programme' — which turned out to be Vortex's cover for acquiring shrunken inventory from prisons. His rage at being deceived dominates his final moments more than fear. When Cassandra lifts him to her mouth, he is already plotting his angle, using her name to briefly freeze her — a tactic that almost works, before she dismisses him as a stranger. His final moments are in Cassandra's mouth, washed down with a gulp of coffee. His dominant trait is outraged disbelief rather than terror." },
  { id:'nicole-barnes', name:'Nicole Barnes', birthday:'Unknown', gender:'Female', nationality:'US American', occupation:'Convicted robber', hair:'Unknown', eyes:'Unknown', height:'Unknown', weight:'Unknown', chest:'Unknown', waist:'Unknown', hips:'Unknown', firstAppearance:'Checking Out', status:'deceased', setting:'Shrunken / Prey', stories:['Checking Out'], deathCause:"Eaten by Victoria Lindquist while she speaks to Cassandra; sucked off tongue and swallowed mid-conversation", killer:'Victoria Lindquist', intelligence:55, fear:90, vocalness:95, obedient:5, desire:0, iconicQuote:'"Please! I\'m sorry! I know I\'m a bad person! But please, forgive me!" — Nicole Barnes as Victoria prepares to swallow her, Checking Out', bio:"Nicole Barnes led a series of robberies on gas stations and convenience stores and was serving time in the same prison as Joe Gunderson when Vortex's rehabilitation programme swept her up. She is the only shrinkie in Checking Out who explicitly admits wrongdoing and begs for forgiveness — which briefly catches Victoria off-guard, reminding her of her first difficult experience eating tinies as a teenager. Victoria suppresses the pang of guilt and swallows Nicole in an elevator while a family stands nearby, their young daughter staring open-mouthed. Her plea — one of the most direct moments of moral acknowledgement from any prey character — still achieves nothing. Her fate is sealed regardless." },
  { id:'scott-chapman', name:'Scott Chapman', birthday:'Unknown', gender:'Male', nationality:'US American', occupation:'Stock trader / Fraudster', hair:'Unknown', eyes:'Unknown', height:'Unknown', weight:'Unknown', chest:'Unknown', waist:'Unknown', hips:'Unknown', firstAppearance:'Checking Out', status:'deceased', setting:'Shrunken / Prey', stories:['Checking Out'], deathCause:"Played with in Victoria's mouth during bath, then swallowed while she drinks hot chocolate", killer:'Victoria Lindquist', intelligence:50, fear:90, vocalness:90, obedient:5, desire:0, iconicQuote:'"NOT ME! I\'M NOT READY! I\'M N—" — Scott Chapman as Victoria drops him into her mouth, Checking Out', bio:"Scott Chapman graduated from an elite university with an MBA and quickly became a rising star at the stock exchange, spending nearly a decade in an endless blur of parties, drugs, and embezzlement, before being arrested on the same day his firm filed for bankruptcy. He was the kind of person who wouldn't have given Victoria a second glance had she brought him drinks. Now he is the first named shrinkie she consumes in her bath — played around in her cheek for a prolonged moment before being swallowed. The story notes the profound irony that this man, who had objectified women throughout his adult life, meets his end as the snack of a hotel receptionist he would have dismissed." },
  { id:'marcus-chen', name:'Marcus Chen', birthday:'Unknown', gender:'Male', nationality:'US American', occupation:'Firefighter (convicted arsonist)', hair:'Unknown', eyes:'Unknown', height:'Unknown', weight:'Unknown', chest:'Unknown', waist:'Unknown', hips:'Unknown', firstAppearance:'Checking Out', status:'deceased', setting:'Shrunken / Prey', stories:['Checking Out'], deathCause:"Swallowed by Victoria Lindquist during her bath conditioner routine", killer:'Victoria Lindquist', intelligence:35, fear:90, vocalness:70, obedient:10, desire:0, iconicQuote:'"[Screaming as Victoria reaches into the box]" — Marcus Chen, Checking Out', bio:"Marcus Chen was a firefighter from the Rust Belt who had set fire to a house in order to make a name for himself professionally, nearly killing an elderly woman in the process. He is consumed by Victoria during the two-minute wait for her conditioner to seep in — eaten almost as a time-filler. The story presents him as a tragic contradiction: a man whose supposed vocation was to save lives, whose final act of selfishness cost him everything." },
  { id:'harper-bennett', name:'Harper Bennett', birthday:'Unknown', gender:'Female', nationality:'US American', occupation:'Wildlife activist', hair:'Unknown', eyes:'Unknown', height:'Unknown', weight:'Unknown', chest:'Unknown', waist:'Unknown', hips:'Unknown', firstAppearance:'Checking Out', status:'deceased', setting:'Shrunken / Prey', stories:['Checking Out'], deathCause:"Flicked into Victoria's mouth and swallowed during conditioner rinse", killer:'Victoria Lindquist', intelligence:60, fear:90, vocalness:80, obedient:5, desire:0, iconicQuote:'"[Eaten without acknowledgement as Victoria rinses her conditioner]" — Harper Bennett, Checking Out', bio:"Harper Bennett was a young wildlife activist from the Pacific Northwest who had made an enemy in a politician trying to advance his career by routing a highway through a protected nature reserve. Leveraging his Vortex contacts, the politician had her quietly disappeared. She is one of the most unambiguously innocent victims in the series — someone who ends up in a Vortex box not for any crime, but for standing in the way of the powerful. Victoria never learns any of this, flicking her into her mouth and swallowing her mid-routine without a second thought." },
  { id:'monica-baker', name:'Monica Baker', birthday:'Unknown', gender:'Female', nationality:'US American', occupation:'State prosecutor\'s attorney', hair:'Unknown', eyes:'Unknown', height:'Unknown', weight:'Unknown', chest:'Unknown', waist:'Unknown', hips:'Unknown', firstAppearance:'Checking Out', status:'deceased', setting:'Shrunken / Prey', stories:['Checking Out'], deathCause:"Swallowed whole by Hannah Lindquist in a spoonful of fruity loops cereal; digested alive for nearly an hour", killer:'Hannah Lindquist', intelligence:75, fear:95, vocalness:90, obedient:5, desire:0, iconicQuote:'"[Crying softly on the spoon, hugging Alex as Hannah raises it to her mouth]" — Monica Baker, Checking Out', bio:"Monica Baker was an up-and-coming attorney at a state prosecutor's office who had been quietly investigating questionable financial transactions from offshore companies to various politicians. This investigation ended not only her career but her life — Vortex was deployed to make her disappear, and her husband Alex was taken simply for being married to her. She is eaten by Hannah Lindquist in a spoonful of fruity loops cereal during a video call with Victoria. She and Alex are described clinging to each other on the spoon, crying softly — one of the most quietly devastating moments in the series. She is swallowed whole and spends almost an hour dying inside Hannah's stomach. Her case and the corruption she was investigating vanish with her." },
  { id:'alex-baker', name:'Alex Baker', birthday:'Unknown', gender:'Male', nationality:'US American', occupation:'Unknown', hair:'Unknown', eyes:'Unknown', height:'Unknown', weight:'Unknown', chest:'Unknown', waist:'Unknown', hips:'Unknown', firstAppearance:'Checking Out', status:'deceased', setting:'Shrunken / Prey', stories:['Checking Out'], deathCause:"Crushed between Hannah Lindquist's molars; killed instantly by a bite", killer:'Hannah Lindquist', intelligence:40, fear:95, vocalness:65, obedient:10, desire:0, iconicQuote:'"[Clinging to Monica on the spoon as Hannah raises it to her mouth]" — Alex Baker, Checking Out', bio:"Alex Baker had the misfortune of being married to Monica Baker, an attorney investigating political corruption. When Vortex came for her, Alex was taken as well — collateral damage. He and Monica are described hugging each other on Hannah's cereal spoon, crying softly, as Hannah's mouth opens above them. Alex's torso is crushed between Hannah's molars as she bites down on the spoonful of cereal; his death is swift. Monica, however, is swallowed whole. Their story is a quiet indictment of how the Vortex system eliminates entire lives to protect the powerful." },
  { id:'kyle-edwards', name:'Kyle Edwards', birthday:'Unknown', gender:'Male', nationality:'US American', occupation:'Unknown', hair:'Unknown', eyes:'Unknown', height:'Unknown', weight:'Unknown', chest:'Unknown', waist:'Unknown', hips:'Unknown', firstAppearance:'Checking Out', status:'deceased', setting:'Shrunken / Prey', stories:['Checking Out'], deathCause:"Survived Victoria's bath session; given to Stacy (Ryan's wife) two days later and eaten by her", killer:'Stacy (Ryan\'s wife)', intelligence:40, fear:100, vocalness:100, obedient:0, desire:0, iconicQuote:'"[Hammering his fists against his cubicle window, watching Victoria eat his brother]" — Kyle Edwards, Checking Out', bio:"Kyle Edwards is the brother of the unnamed shrinkie Victoria swallowed immediately before him in the bath — making him the only character in Checking Out who witnesses a direct family member being consumed. He breaks down in tears as Victoria yawns, giving him a view of the back of her throat. Unlike most of the box's occupants, he survives Victoria's bath session because she puts the remaining box on her pantry shelf. Two days later, Victoria offers him to Stacy — Ryan Lindquist's wife, a nurse — who drops by to pick up a forgotten scarf. He meets his end in Stacy's stomach, the story noting this without ceremony. His survival is not salvation; only a postponement." },
  { id:'checking-out-main-character', name:'Checking Out Main Character', birthday:'Unknown', gender:'Male', nationality:'US American', occupation:'Business traveller', hair:'Unknown', eyes:'Unknown', height:'Unknown', weight:'Unknown', chest:'Unknown', waist:'Unknown', hips:'Unknown', firstAppearance:'Checking Out', status:'deceased', setting:'Shrunken / Prey', stories:['Checking Out'], deathCause:"Swept into Victoria Lindquist's mouth with a wave of bathwater during a shark-dive manoeuvre; digested overnight and flushed at 11 PM the same evening", killer:'Victoria Lindquist', intelligence:65, fear:98, vocalness:85, obedient:10, desire:60, iconicQuote:'"Victoria, please! It\'s me! We met at the hotel! Don\'t do this!" — screaming up at her from the bathwater, Checking Out', bio:"The protagonist of Checking Out is a middle-aged male business traveller — the reader is \"you.\" He has been in a Midwestern city for a week of inconsequential meetings, staying at the Grand Imperial Hotel. He woke to a 6 AM wake-up call from Victoria at the front desk, took a shower, packed his bags, and checked out that morning — sharing a genuine, charged flirtation with her across the reception desk that both of them felt. He was walking to his rental car in the underground parking garage when a Vortex operative in a black van stunned him with a cattle prod and took him. He woke already shrunk and packaged inside a Vortex box in the hotel staff room, with no memory of the shrinking itself.\n\nFrom inside the box he watched Cassandra eat Joe Gunderson with her morning coffee and recognised her — she was a hotel employee he had chatted with during his stay. He deduced from the staff shift schedule that his only real hope was if Victoria took his box home, since she was the only one who might recognise him. When she did, he was carried home in her handbag, battered against the walls repeatedly, and watched Hannah eat the Bakers during the video call — at one point slamming his fists on the plastic and screaming \"WE ARE PEOPLE\" at the two women.\n\nIn the bath, a large, powerful Black man in an adjacent cubicle managed to scale the wall and reached down to pull him out, intending to escape together. The protagonist grabbed his hand. Victoria spotted them immediately and snatched them both up. Even dangling over her open mouth, he screamed her name and waved his free arm. She didn't hear him. The man shoved him free — he tumbled across Victoria's chin and bounced off her left breast, splashing into the bathwater below. He resurfaced and tried again: \"Victoria, please! It's me! We met at the hotel! Don't do this!\" — and she heard something, but paused only to give him an amused, sly grin before sliding beneath the surface. She erupted from the water directly beneath him — mouth open wide, all teeth and tongue — scooping him in along with a wave of lavender-scented bathwater. She swallowed immediately, grimacing at the soapy taste, thumped her chest, and said \"ew\" to herself.\n\nHe died inside her stomach over the following hours — conscious through most of his dissolution, screaming into the dark. He expired sometime before she fell asleep reading. His physical remains were flushed at 11 PM that evening when Victoria used the staff toilet before her night shift, embedded in a log of waste alongside the other shrinkies. His flight home took off without him. The airline crew assumed he had overslept. Nobody ever found out what happened to him. He never learned Victoria's last name." },
  { id:'felix', name:'Felix', birthday:'Unknown', gender:'Male', nationality:'German', occupation:'Student', hair:'Unknown', eyes:'Unknown', height:'Unknown', weight:'Unknown', chest:'Unknown', waist:'Unknown', hips:'Unknown', firstAppearance:'Take-out', status:'deceased', setting:'Shrunken / Prey', stories:['Take-out'], deathCause:'Swallowed whole by Julia Böhm while she watched a series on her laptop; digested overnight and flushed the following morning', killer:'Julia Böhm', intelligence:90, fear:60, vocalness:55, obedient:5, desire:20, iconicQuote:'"We need to stay calm and find a way out of here." — Felix to Yannik through the crack in their cubicle wall, Take-out', bio:"Felix is the primary prey perspective character of Take-out and arguably the most strategically capable shrunken character in the German Setting. He is a German student who was shrunk by Vortex after trespassing into a park with his friends Yannik and Daniel, who had wanted to smoke cannabis. He wakes inside a Vortex medium box in the display window of a Vortex restaurant and spends the entire day there, watching giant pedestrians pass before Julia selects his box.\n\nThroughout the ordeal, Felix maintains remarkable composure. He identifies the air-hole foil as the box's weakest point early on, works methodically at exploiting it, communicates with Yannik through a hairline manufacturing crack, deduces Daniel's location by silhouette, and makes multiple coordinated escape attempts. He never gives in to panic the way Yannik does. He is, however, unable to prevent the escape from failing — the box tilts in Julia's handbag, bringing the foil within reach, but she retrieves it before Yannik fully exits. He watches Daniel be eaten by Bahar, and by the time Julia's fingers reach into his cubicle, he describes his terror having burned out into a kind of grim resignation.\n\nInside Julia's mouth, he attempts one final futile kick before being swallowed. He remains conscious through much of his passage down her oesophagus and into her stomach, where he eventually loses consciousness after a flood of Coke sweeps him away. He dies in the dark. By morning, his remains have been converted into fat deposits on Julia's body. She flushes his indigestible remnants during her morning bathroom routine, without thought or memory of him." },
  { id:'yannik', name:'Yannik', birthday:'Unknown', gender:'Male', nationality:'German', occupation:'Student', hair:'Unknown', eyes:'Unknown', height:'Unknown', weight:'Unknown', chest:'Unknown', waist:'Unknown', hips:'Unknown', firstAppearance:'Take-out', status:'deceased', setting:'Shrunken / Prey', stories:['Take-out'], deathCause:"Swallowed whole by Julia Böhm; digested overnight and flushed the following morning — skull vaguely discernible in her waste", killer:'Julia Böhm', intelligence:60, fear:95, vocalness:90, obedient:5, desire:10, iconicQuote:'"You\'ve said that a thousand times!" — Yannik\'s frightened, brittle voice through the cubicle crack, Take-out', bio:"Yannik is Felix's friend and the prey character sharing the cubicle wall with him in Take-out. He was in the park with Felix and Daniel when Vortex found them. Throughout the story he is the emotional opposite of Felix: where Felix is controlled and strategic, Yannik is terrified, brittle, and frequently on the edge of tears. He cries audibly, snaps at Felix's reassurances, and struggles to maintain composure.\n\nHe is, however, the one who achieves the closest thing to a physical breakthrough — he finds a tear forming in his air-hole foil and is actively squeezing through it when Julia's hand plunges into her handbag and retrieves the box, sending him sliding back onto the floor of his cubicle. The moment is the story's closest thing to an escape, and its sudden reversal is devastating.\n\nYannik is swallowed by Julia towards the end of her evening, a casual gulp while watching the season finale of her series. He is digested overnight. The following morning, Julia's waste is described as containing what appears to be the outline of Yannik's skull — a pale skeletal face frozen in a silent scream — pressed into the faecal mass. Julia wipes without noticing and flushes without a thought." },
  { id:'daniel', name:'Daniel', birthday:'Unknown', gender:'Male', nationality:'German', occupation:'Student', hair:'Unknown', eyes:'Unknown', height:'Unknown', weight:'Unknown', chest:'Unknown', waist:'Unknown', hips:'Unknown', firstAppearance:'Take-out', status:'deceased', setting:'Shrunken / Prey', stories:['Take-out'], deathCause:"Tossed into Bahar Esfahani's mouth as a stolen 'dessert' shrinkie and swallowed; digested overnight and flushed next morning", killer:'Bahar Esfahani', intelligence:75, fear:70, vocalness:40, obedient:5, desire:15, iconicQuote:'"This kind of sucks. How about we get the hell out of here?" — Daniel, dry and exhausted, reaching down to Felix from the cubicle wall, Take-out', bio:"Daniel is Felix's best friend since kindergarten — described by Felix as close enough that watching him be eaten is one of the most shattering moments of the story. He is an athletic German student who was in the park with Felix and Yannik the night they were taken. He ends up in the cubicle directly above Felix and, in a feat of sheer determination, manages to haul himself up to the top edge of the dividing wall — trembling from the effort — and reaches down to pull Felix out. His delivery ('This kind of sucks. How about we get the hell out of here?') is dry, exhausted, and remarkably composed.\n\nThe rescue attempt ends when Bahar's fingers close around him mid-effort. He is lifted away just as Felix grabs his hand — Felix lets go at the last moment out of animal survival instinct, falling back into his cubicle and cracking a rib. Daniel, pinned by Bahar's fingers, is carried up to her face and tossed into her mouth without ceremony. She was stealing a single shrinkie from Julia's box as 'dessert' after her own dinner out.\n\nDaniel fights inside her mouth — kicks, struggles — but is swallowed within seconds. He remains alive for some time inside Bahar's stomach, clawing his way over the half-digested Pad Thai remnants of her earlier dinner, trying to avoid the acidic pools. When Bahar stretches at her desk — shifting her stomach contents — he is swept into an acid pool and dies. By morning, over 90% of what was once Daniel has been absorbed into Bahar's body, primarily deposited as fat. She flushes his remaining trace the following morning without the slightest awareness." },
  { id:'christian-lange', name:'Christian Lange', birthday:'Unknown', gender:'Male', nationality:'German', occupation:'Journalist / Economist', hair:'Unknown', eyes:'Unknown', height:'Unknown', weight:'Unknown', chest:'Unknown', waist:'Unknown', hips:'Unknown', firstAppearance:'Take-out', status:'deceased', setting:'Shrunken / Prey', stories:['Take-out'], deathCause:"Plucked from box by Julia Böhm's fingernails and swallowed whole without being looked at; first shrinkie she ate that evening", killer:'Julia Böhm', intelligence:55, fear:90, vocalness:80, obedient:5, desire:0, iconicQuote:'"[Flailing and cursing at Julia\'s fingernails as she plucks him from the box without looking]" — Christian Lange, Take-out', bio:"Christian Lange is a named German victim in Take-out, described as a rising star in the economics section of a prestigious newspaper. Months before his death, Julia had read one of his articles online — an insightful piece about current economic growth in China — while preparing for a university presentation. She has no idea that the author of that paper is the first shrinkie she reaches for when she opens the box that evening. She doesn't look at him. She plucks him by the collar with her fingernails, he flails and curses at her, she drops him into her mouth and swallows him whole. The interaction — from Julia's side — is entirely absent-minded. The dark irony that Julia had actively engaged with his intellectual work, found it useful, and is now consuming him without a second thought is one of the story's quietest and most pointed commentaries on the Vortex world." },
  { id:'nadine-kowalczyk', name:'Nadine Kowalczyk', birthday:'Unknown', gender:'Female', nationality:'German', occupation:'Student (graphic design)', hair:'Unknown', eyes:'Unknown', height:'Unknown', weight:'Unknown', chest:'Unknown', waist:'Unknown', hips:'Unknown', firstAppearance:'Take-out', status:'deceased', setting:'Shrunken / Prey', stories:['Take-out'], deathCause:"Fell from Julia's fingers into her cleavage after collar tore; fished out and swallowed. Near-choked Julia slightly", killer:'Julia Böhm', intelligence:35, fear:100, vocalness:100, obedient:0, desire:0, iconicQuote:'"[Screaming and begging at the towering woman, voice too small to be heard]" — Nadine Kowalczyk, Take-out', bio:"Nadine Kowalczyk is a German graphic design student from a nearby city and one of the more unusual victims in the series. She belonged to an online community secretly aroused by the idea of being shrunken and eaten — vore enthusiasts — and had submitted her name to a 'Vortex Volunteers' list she believed to be a joke post on one of her forums. It was not a joke. The post had been planted by the Strategic Enforcement Division of Vortex, who added her to their inventory with no further process required. In Nadine's case specifically, the story notes that Vortex considered her 'sick desires' alone sufficient justification.\n\nNadine had once found scenarios like this thrilling in fantasy. Reality is something else entirely. When Julia reaches for her, she is overwhelmed by blind panic — she cannot even recall her former excitement. She screams and begs, but her voice cannot reach Julia. Julia flicks her toward her mouth, the collar tears, and Nadine plummets straight into Julia's cleavage. Julia rolls her eyes, fishes around with mild embarrassment, pinches Nadine out, and this time successfully flips her into her mouth. Nadine slides straight down her throat from sheer momentum, nearly causing Julia to choke. Julia clears her throat with a gulp of Coke, suppresses a small belch, and licks her lips. She is the only named victim in Take-out who arguably brought her circumstances upon herself — though the terror she experiences in her final moments suggests her fantasy offered no comfort whatsoever." },
  { id:'live-feeding-main-character', name:'Live Feeding Main Character', birthday:'Unknown', gender:'Male', nationality:'Unknown', occupation:'Unknown', hair:'Unknown', eyes:'Unknown', height:'Unknown', weight:'Unknown', chest:'Unknown', waist:'Unknown', hips:'Unknown', firstAppearance:'Live Feeding', status:'deceased', setting:'Shrunken / Prey', stories:['Live Feeding'], deathCause:'Dipped in sweet and sour sauce and swallowed whole by Amina Tijani as the last shrinkie of her livestream; digested overnight and expelled the following morning', killer:'Amina Tijani', intelligence:55, fear:95, vocalness:80, obedient:5, desire:20, iconicQuote:'"I\'m innocent! Please, Amina, don\'t eat me! I didn\'t do anyth—" — The protagonist\'s final words, cut off as Amina parts her lips, Live Feeding', bio:'The Live Feeding Main Character is the unnamed second-person protagonist of Live Feeding, addressed throughout as "you." He is male, his background and occupation unknown. He is one of many shrinkies packed into a Vortex box inside a restaurant storage room, where he first regains consciousness.\n\nHe witnesses Laura Giesler eating casually from her personal box on her lunch break, then watches Anna Wendland steal and eat a shrunken woman who makes desperate eye contact with him — a moment that cements the full hopelessness of his situation. When Anna selects his box for delivery, he is loaded into her delivery bag, tossed about during the bicycle ride across a rainy city, and brought to a penthouse flat whose inhabitant he recognises from her videos: Amina Tijani, the food influencer behind AminaEats.\n\nHe spends the entire livestream watching from his cubicle as Amina methodically eats the other shrinkies one by one — dipping them in sauces, commenting on flavour pairings, patting her belly and talking about the tingle of them wriggling inside her. He is the last one left, and he attempts to stay completely still and avoid her notice. A viewer spots him in the chat and alerts her. She reaches in, pins him between her fingers, and dips him into sweet and sour sauce. He screams that he is innocent, pleads with her by name — but she either cannot hear him or does not acknowledge him in the slightest, her eyes on the chat. She places him on her lower lip, sucks him in, rolls him across her tongue, and swallows.\n\nHis internal experience of digestion is the most detailed in the series: the crushing pressure of the oesophagus, the acrid stench of the stomach, the tsunami of Coke flooding in above him, the burning of stomach acid, the faint sobbing of the other shrinkies in the dark, and finally his losing consciousness as oxygen runs out. By morning he has been fully absorbed — the narrative notes that the majority of what was once him has been deposited as fat in Amina\'s buttocks. His bleached bone fragments are expelled and flushed without a glance. She is already thinking about avocado toast.' }
];

const germanStories = [
  { id:'take-out', title:'Take-out', order:1, chars:['Julia Böhm','Bahar Esfahani','Laura Giesler','Philipp','Felix (shrunken)','Yannik (shrunken)','Daniel (shrunken)','Christian Lange (shrunken)','Nadine Kowalczyk (shrunken)'], desc:'The first German Setting story and the entry point to the entire universe. Julia Böhm purchases a medium Vortex box (48 shrinkies) from a Vortex restaurant on a winter evening, accompanied by classmate Philipp — who harbours both romantic feelings for her and a quiet, unspoken moral unease about Vortex. The story alternates between their casual conversation on the icy streets and the desperate perspective of Felix, a shrunken German student trapped inside the display box with his friends Yannik and Daniel. As Julia walks home, carries the box in her handbag, changes into pyjamas, and settles onto her sofa bed with her laptop and a glass of Coke, Felix makes increasingly desperate escape attempts — communicating with Yannik through a hairline crack, working at the foil seal, coordinating with Daniel to escape via the cubicle walls. Julia eats through the box entirely over the course of an episode and a season finale, never once looking at what she is eating. Bahar arrives home and steals one shrinkie as "dessert" — Daniel, Felix\'s best friend since kindergarten, eaten casually and without ceremony. By morning, there is nothing left. The story\'s title is both literal and allegorical: the world of VortexFoods™ told in a single take-out order.' },
  { id:'live-feeding', title:'Live Feeding', order:2, chars:['Laura Giesler','Anna Wendland','Amina Tijani','Live Feeding Main Character (shrunken)'], desc:'A second-person narrative told from the perspective of a shrunken "you," opening in a Vortex restaurant storage area. The protagonist wakes inside a cubicle of a Vortex box, already shrunken and dressed in a black coverall, surrounded by the screams of others in the same condition. Laura Giesler is observed eating shrinkies on her lunch break — casually swallowing a man alive, then a hysterically crying woman, treating both as inconsequential snacks while chatting with delivery driver Anna Wendland. Anna steals one shrinkie from Laura\'s box — a woman who makes eye contact with the protagonist — and eats her with appreciative relish before slipping the protagonist\'s box into her delivery bag and cycling through a rainy midday city to a penthouse flat. The customer is Amina Tijani, a well-known Nigerian-German food influencer who livestreams her entire meal to thousands of viewers. She orders the full Vortex cheeseburger menu alongside a medium box (48 shrinkies) and all available sauces, and spends the stream reviewing flavour pairings — dipping shrinkies in ketchup, mayo, spicy sauce, yoghurt dip, and sweet and sour, while enthusiastically describing the "tingle" she feels as they slide down her throat and wriggle in her stomach. The protagonist watches from the box as one by one the other shrinkies are consumed. Near the end of the stream a viewer alerts Amina to the last remaining shrinkie — the protagonist — cowering in their cubicle. She dips them in sweet and sour sauce, savours them briefly, and swallows. The final third of the story follows the digestion sequence in graphic physiological detail through the evening, night, and into the following morning, concluding with the protagonist\'s remains expelled and flushed. Amina is already thinking about avocado toast.' },
  { id:'beyond-the-sea', title:'Beyond the Sea', order:3, chars:['Bahar Esfahani','Johanna von Falkenau'], desc:'Bahar Esfahani takes a trip with Johanna von Falkenau, introducing the von Falkenau family into the German Setting storyline and expanding the social world of the main characters beyond the university setting.' },
  { id:'the-study-session', title:'The Study Session', order:4, chars:['Julia Böhm','Bahar Esfahani'], desc:'Julia and Bahar engage in a study session, with VortexFoods™ products likely playing a role in the domestic setting. The story explores the characters in a quieter, more intimate context.' },
  { id:'quality-assurance', title:'Quality Assurance', order:5, chars:['Andrea Thiele','Sabrina Kramer','Jennifer Dietz','Alexander Behrens'], desc:'A Vortex corporate story. Department managers at the consulting firm Reinhold & Becker are subjected to a dressing-down over their handling of Vortex logistics contracts. A representative of VortexFoods™ arrives to settle the dispute in a definitively Vortex fashion. Sabrina Kramer, Jennifer Dietz, and Andrea Thiele are central to the corporate side of the story.' },
  { id:'swim-practice', title:'Swim Practice', order:6, chars:['Moritz Karalis','Annika Zöllner'], desc:'A story set at a swimming pool or during swim training, following Moritz Karalis and Annika Zöllner.' },
  { id:'a-saturday-in-town', title:'A Saturday in Town', order:7, chars:['Tanja Hofer','Lisa Mayer','Jessica Seibert','Alessia Santoro'], desc:'The social circle of Tanja, Lisa, Jessica, and Alessia spends a Saturday in the city, with VortexFoods™ featuring as part of their consumer habits during a day out.' },
  { id:'an-afternoon-at-the-pool', title:'An Afternoon at the Pool', order:8, chars:['Konstantin von Falkenau','Johanna von Falkenau','Claudia Santoro','Alessia Santoro'], desc:'The von Falkenau siblings and their social circle spend an afternoon at a public pool. Claudia Santoro and her daughter Alessia are also present, expanding the Santoro family\'s role in the German Setting.' },
  { id:'drive-through', title:'Drive-through', order:9, chars:['Birgit Kohler','Florian Kohler'], desc:'A drive-through VortexFoods™ restaurant story featuring Birgit and Florian Kohler.' },
  { id:'the-drinking-game', title:'The Drinking Game', order:10, chars:['Sebastian Kemp'], desc:'A social gathering involving a drinking game, with VortexFoods™ products incorporated into the event.' },
  { id:'a-helping-hand', title:'A Helping Hand', order:11, chars:['Agnieszka Wójcik'], desc:'Agnieszka Wójcik, a Polish cleaning lady, appears in a story whose title suggests an act of assistance, potentially involving shrinkies or someone caught in a dangerous situation.' },
  { id:'girls-night-out', title:'Girls\' Night Out', order:12, chars:['Tanja Hofer','Lisa Mayer','Marie Krüger','Josephine Dubois','Susanne Hofer'], desc:'A girls\' night out featuring a social group including Tanja, Lisa, Marie Krüger, Josephine Dubois, and Susanne Hofer. VortexFoods™ products are likely part of the evening\'s entertainment.' },
  { id:'a-balanced-breakfast', title:'A Balanced Breakfast', order:13, chars:['Julia Böhm','Bahar Esfahani'], desc:'Julia and Bahar start their day with a breakfast that includes VortexFoods™ products, exploring the casual domesticity of shrinkie consumption.' },
  { id:'hide-and-seek', title:'Hide and Seek', order:14, chars:['Pia Hinz','Niklas Faber','Kerstin Lüdtke'], desc:'A story involving Pia Hinz, Niklas Faber, and teacher Kerstin Lüdtke. The "hide and seek" of the title likely refers to shrinkies attempting to hide from or evade being found by the normal-sized characters.' },
  { id:'stomach-bug', title:'Stomach Bug', order:15, chars:['Bettina Mayer'], desc:'Physician Bettina Mayer features in this story, whose title likely references a digestive situation connected to shrinkie consumption.' },
  { id:'with-friends-like-these', title:'With Friends Like These', order:16, chars:['Marie Krüger','Isabel Buchner','Carolin Reuter','Nadine Scholz','Eva Wagner','Kim Reineke','Thorsten Henschel','Piero Santoro'], desc:'A darker entry in the German Setting involving a school social environment with Marie Krüger at the centre. The story also introduces paramilitary figures Kim Reineke and Thorsten Henschel, as well as diplomat Piero Santoro, suggesting escalating stakes and institutional complicity.' },
  { id:'all-in-the-family-1', title:'All in the Family (Part 1)', order:17, chars:['Alessia Santoro','Claudia Santoro','Piero Santoro','Marco Santoro','Cornelia Borsig','Cecilia Pellegrino','Lucia Pellegrino'], desc:'The first part of a two-part story centring on the Santoro family. Stefan — a male character who has romantic feelings for Alessia — finds himself shrunken. The opening scene shows him begging Alessia not to eat him as she looms over him, having already consumed several other shrinkies. Her reaction — pulling back, confused and disturbed — sets up the emotional core of the story.' },
  { id:'all-in-the-family-2', title:'All in the Family (Part 2)', order:18, chars:['Alessia Santoro','Claudia Santoro','Piero Santoro','Marco Santoro','Cornelia Borsig','Cecilia Pellegrino','Lucia Pellegrino'], desc:'The conclusion of the All in the Family story, continuing Stefan\'s ordeal in the Santoro household and resolving the emotional tension set up in Part 1.' },
  { id:'dinner-party', title:'Dinner Party', order:19, chars:['Richard von Falkenau','Sophie von Falkenau','Johanna von Falkenau','Konstantin von Falkenau','Roland Hofer','Susanne Hofer','Friedrich Theissen','Eliska Bieliková-Theissen','Persephone Carrendon-Wexley','Felicity Carrendon-Wexley','Lucia Pellegrino','Alessia Santoro','Piero Santoro'], desc:'The final German Setting story (to date) and its most expansive in terms of cast. The von Falkenau family hosts a grand dinner party attended by an international assembly of aristocrats, diplomats, businesspeople, and socialites. VortexFoods™ shrinkies feature as part of the evening\'s luxury entertainment. The story opens from the perspective of Olivia, a shrunken person who wakes in a prison-like holding cell as the dinner approaches.' },
];

const americanStories = [
  { id:'strange-behaviours', title:'Strange Behaviours', order:1, chars:['Ashley Taylor','Mary Taylor','Robert Taylor','Rachel Cohen (mentioned)','Brian (shrunken)','Megan Sanders (shrunken)','Timothy Walker (shrunken)'], desc:'The first American Setting story, told from dual perspectives: primarily from Brian, a shrunken vorarephile, and secondarily from Ashley Taylor herself. Brian is trapped in a Vortex box on Ashley\'s desk in her room, watching in horror and arousal as she casually snacks on the other shrinkies while studying German. The story culminates in Brian\'s unusual request and the graphic account of his death by digestion. Ashley\'s parents Mary and Robert are introduced, with a background argument hinting at Mary\'s moral objections to Vortex.' },
  { id:'an-american-nightmare', title:'An American Nightmare', order:2, chars:['Ashley Taylor','Mary Taylor','Robert Taylor','Max (shrunken)','Kayla Hayes','Megan Smith','Kelly Lewis','Ulrike Grimm','Alfred Hoffmann'], desc:'Max, a German student opposed to VortexFoods™, meets Ashley Taylor at an airport. He is arrested for drug possession and handed to Vortex operatives under "Section V", shrunk, and placed into the in-flight catering supply of the very plane Ashley boards. The story follows Max\'s terror inside the catering trolley, witnessing Kelly Lewis eat Thilo Busch, and his ultimate fate — swallowed unknowingly by Ashley during the in-flight promotional dinner. Ashley never learns the truth.' },
  { id:'a-matter-of-principle', title:'A Matter of Principle', order:3, chars:['Paige Wright (shrunken)','Dylan (shrunken)','Jordan (shrunken)','Miguel (shrunken)','Tyler (shrunken)','Diane (shrunken)','Kayla Hayes','Seo-Yun Park','Mark Campbell','Rachel Cohen','Ashley Taylor','Hannah Lindquist','Maria Reyes Ortega'], desc:'The most politically charged story in the American Setting. Paige Wright and her brother Dylan, along with around a dozen comrades including Jordan, Miguel, and Tyler, stage a night raid on one of Vortex\'s largest North American processing centres. Their mission is sabotaged from within — their embedded comrade Seo-Yun Park is revealed to be a Vortex informant — and the group is captured by Kayla Hayes and her paramilitary detail. Rather than face a trial, they are sent to processing and shrunken. Paige, Dylan, Jordan, and others end up in a Vortex display counter at a beachfront restaurant. The story\'s second half follows Hannah Lindquist, an incoming college freshman, as she eats her first ever shrinkie — with Paige becoming Hannah\'s first victim, swallowed whole after an intense internal moral struggle that turns out to be arousal rather than conscience. Rachel Cohen, meanwhile, eats Miguel and nearly eats Paige herself. Ashley Taylor swallows Dylan after learning who he is. The story ends with Hannah sleeping contentedly as her body digests her first dozen victims.' },
  { id:'good-for-goodness-sake', title:"Good for Goodness' Sake", order:4, chars:['Hannah Lindquist','Victoria Lindquist','William Lindquist','Ryan Lindquist','Arthur (shrunken)'], desc:"The fourth American Setting story, set entirely on Christmas Eve and Christmas Day in the Lindquist family's snowy hometown near the Canadian border. Hannah returns home after months at university during which she has consumed hundreds of shrinkies and is now a seasoned, sexually experienced predator. She buys a small box of shrinkies at the airport to snack on during her journey. Back in her old room, she empties them onto her mother's Christmas cookie plate and begins eating. Her older sister Victoria barges in and casually helps herself to around a dozen without a second thought, accidentally biting down on one tucked inside a piece of gingerbread and swallowing it with mild surprise. Hannah then recognises Arthur — a former classmate with a long-standing crush on her — among the remaining tinies. The story shifts to dual perspective as Arthur's dawning hope and Hannah's equally dawning predatory arousal are explored in parallel. Rather than spare him, Hannah inserts him into her vagina and uses him through an intense orgasm, then carries him inside her through Christmas Eve dinner with the entire family. Late that night she retrieves him, conducts a brief, final conversation, and swallows him whole while climaxing. The story's concluding pages follow Arthur's digestion in graphic physiological detail through the night, ending with his remains flushed away Christmas morning. The title references the Christmas carol 'Santa Claus is Coming to Town,' which plays in the background as Hannah swallows Arthur." },
  { id:'checking-out', title:'Checking Out', order:5, chars:['Victoria Lindquist','Cassandra Davis','Checking Out Main Character (shrunken)','Hannah Lindquist','Nicole Barnes (shrunken)','Scott Chapman (shrunken)','Marcus Chen (shrunken)','Harper Bennett (shrunken)','Monica Baker (shrunken)','Alex Baker (shrunken)','Joe Gunderson (shrunken)','Kyle Edwards (shrunken)'], desc:'A second-person story set in a Midwestern city hotel during a February snowstorm. The protagonist — a middle-aged male business traveller addressed as "you" — is woken at 6 AM by Victoria Lindquist\'s warm voice for his checkout call. He showers, packs, and heads down to the empty lobby, sharing a genuine mutual flirtation with Victoria across the front desk before heading to the parking garage. There he is stunned with a cattle prod by a Vortex operative in a black van and wakes up already shrunken inside a Vortex box in the hotel staff room. The story interweaves four perspectives: the protagonist inside the box, recognising Cassandra Davis and watching her eat Joe Gunderson with her morning coffee; Victoria processing her checkout and heading home with the box; Hannah on a dawn video call casually eating Monica and Alex Baker in spoonfuls of fruity loops cereal; and Cassandra eating through the rest of the staff box on her break. Victoria eats Nicole Barnes in an elevator on the way to her car. At home she runs a lavender-scented bath and drinks hot chocolate, eating Scott Chapman, Marcus Chen, and Harper Bennett one by one. The protagonist attempts to escape with the help of a fellow shrinkie who scales the dividing wall — Victoria snatches them both, swallows the other man, and when the protagonist falls free into the bath, she submerges and erupts from beneath him in a shark-dive (a move she learned from Stacy), sweeping him into her mouth with the bathwater. She swallows immediately, grimaces at the soapy taste, thumps her chest. She eats one more shrinkie to prevent escape, then shelves the remaining box — including Kyle Edwards, who watches his brother die before him — and goes to bed. The protagonist is digested overnight and flushed at 11 PM when Victoria uses the staff toilet before her next shift. Kyle survives two more days before being given to Stacy.' },
];

